        <title>Inferring a moral matter</title>
        </head>
    <html:body xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit' xmlns:html='http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml'>
        <!-- <<< deindent -->



<postulate_X cog:lid='X'>
    Within the practical horizon, all existential hazards to rational nature are confined
    to smaller volumes of space-time than is rational nature itself, in its human descent
   <script xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit.step'>Script this</script>
    </postulate_X>



<postulate_R cog:lid='R'>
    I value practical reason above all
    </postulate_R>



<moral_matter_M cog:lid='M'>
    In continual fear of proving to be unequal to reason’s demands,
    to be unworthy of my most valued gift, and [unworthy] of the gift giver,
    I readjust my means to — and so reaffirm my devotion to —
    securing the endless continuity of rational nature in the existential refuge of great distances
    <matter>
        <material_end_E cog:lid='E'>
            The endless continuity of rational nature in the existential refuge of great distances
            <step:script xmlns:step='data:,wayscript.bit.step'>
                Script this
                <X cog:link='#X'/>
                </step:script>
            </material_end_E>
        <fear>
            <experience cog:link='/human/fear/#experience'/>
            <interpretations>
                <reasoned cog:link='/human/fear/#logical'/>
                <imagined cog:link='/human/fear/#mythic_imaginary'/>
                <felt cog:link='/human/fear/#felt'/>
                </interpretations>
            </fear>
        <response>
            I readjust my means to — and so reaffirm my devotion to —
            securing the material end <html:a href='#E'>E</html:a>
            <script xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit.step'>Script this</script>
            </response>
        </matter>
    <morality cog:lid='M_as_moral'>
        M is (to me) moral
        <script xmlns='data:,wayscript.bit.step'>Script this</script>
        </morality>
    </moral_matter_M>



